import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Open Prices')
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():.2f}")
    
    plt.xlabel('Open Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of open prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['open'], label='Open', color='blue')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['close'], label='Close', color='red')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Price')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between open and close prices?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    signal_counts = data['signal'].value_counts()
    signal_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green'])
    plt.xlabel('Signal')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'signal' values?", wrap=True)
    plt.legend(signal_counts.index)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
